  "decision_conditions": [
    "It is considered that the scheme would not make optimal use of the sustainable brownfield site due to the provision of a significantly over sized unit, and therefore does not meet the government  objective of significantly boosting housing delivery. As such the proposal is  contrary to Paragraphs 61, 124 and 125 of the NPPF, 2024 and Policies GG2, H1 ,H2, D3, D6 of the London Plan 2021 and CS10 of the Kingston Core Strategy (2012).",
    "Whilst this is not a major development proposal, taking into account reason for refusal No. 1, in that the development has been  artificially constrained to provide 9 units and results in the loss low cost specialist residential accommodation by an affordable housing provider,  the proposal  would be required to provide an appropriate level of affordable housing. The application fails to demonstrate that the scheme has provided the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing, as required by Core Strategy Policies DM15 and CS10 and Policy H4 and H5 of the London Plan (2021).",
    "It is considered that the scheme has not adequately mitigated  for the loss of specialist wheelchair housing and as such is  contrary to Policies H12 and D4 of the London Plan and Policy DM14 and DM24 of the Core Strategy, and paragraphs 61 and 63 of the NPPF.",
    "It has not been demonstrated that the scheme would provide good quality accommodation, particularly in relation to the poor quality private amenity space and lack of play space, and the poor access arrangements. The proposal is contrary to Policies D4 and D6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy DM10 of the Kingston Core Strategy (2012)."
